summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Board of Park Commissioners of the City of Seattle to purchase, for park and parkway purposes, a portion of the south tract in Lot No. 2, Section 10, Township 24 North, of range 4 East W.M., as conveyed to Brown Brothers Lumber Company by William C. Fricke and wife December 21, 1901, and of record in Volume 299 of Deeds, at page 162 in the records of King County, Washington.
